{"id":"2203.01966","submitter":"Gianluca Frasca-Caccia","authors":"Angelamaria Cardone, Gianluca Frasca-Caccia","title":"Numerical conservation laws of time fractional diffusion PDEs","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NA cs.NA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The first part of this paper introduces sufficient conditions to determine\nconservation laws of diffusion equations of arbitrary fractional order in time.\nNumerical methods that satisfy a discrete analogue of these conditions have\nconservation laws that approximate the continuous ones. In the second part of\nthe paper, we propose a method that combines a finite difference method in\nspace with a spectral integrator in time. The time integrator has already been\napplied in literature to solve time fractional equations with Caputo fractional\nderivative of order $\\alpha\\in(0,1)$. It is here generalised to approximate\nCaputo and Riemann-Liouville fractional derivatives of arbitrary order. We\napply the method to subdiffusion and superdiffusion equations with\nRiemann-Liouville fractional derivative and derive its conservation laws.\nFinally, we present a range of numerical experiments to show the convergence of\nthe method and its conservation properties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Mar 2022 19:09:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-07"}
