{"id":"2203.02307","submitter":"Niamh O'Sullivan","authors":"Niamh O'Sullivan","title":"The nilpotent genus of finitely generated residually nilpotent groups","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  If $G$ and $H$ are finitely generated residually nilpotent groups, then $G$\nand $H$ are in the same nilpotent genus if they have the same lower central\nquotients (up to isomorphism). A stronger condition is that $H$ is para-$G$ if\nthere exists a monomorphism of $G$ into $H$ which induces isomorphisms between\nthe corresponding quotients of their lower central series. We first consider\nresidually nilpotent groups and find sufficient conditions on the monomorphism\nso that $H$ is para-$G.$ We then prove that for certain polycyclic groups, if\n$H$ is para-$G$, then $G$ and $H$ have the same Hirsch length. We also prove\nthat the pro-nilpotent completions of these polycyclic groups are locally\npolycyclic.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Mar 2022 13:27:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-07"}
